    <node id="The colonists have to walk all the way to Oasis City because their well has been poisoned, leaving them with no drinkable water. The colony was built on a parched desert wasteland, making the journey to Oasis City their only hope for survival. Additionally, the Kumaji have always resented the colony's presence, as it means one less oasis for their own sustenance. They are pursued by the Kumaji tribe because the tribe has never accepted the colony and has increased the violence of their raids over time. The colonists must hurry on their journey because the Kumaji are after them and Oasis City is their only safe destination, located 500 miles away in the middle of a desert with trackless sands and hundred-and-thirty-degree heat." />
    <node id="1. The old man warned Steve that the Kumaji were looking for the people and wanted to kill them. He urged Steve to hurry because the desert wind would wipe out any evidence of their presence, making it harder for the Kumaji to track them down.&#10;2. Steve gave his canteen to the old man as a gesture of goodwill before he left. The old man had mentioned that he was staying behind and wanted to stay in his home village, so Steve may have felt pity for him and wanted to help him in some way. Additionally, Steve had just rinsed out his mouth with water from the canteen after coming into contact with poisoned sand, so the water in the canteen would have been especially valuable to the old man.&#10;3. Steve reacted to this information by quickly getting himself airborne and flying away without looking back at the deserted village or the old man again. He may have felt a sense of urgency to warn his people about the Kumaji's intentions and to get them to safety as soon as possible." />
