    <node id="Tobias Whiting, the father of Mary Whiting, disappeared during the fourth night of their journey in the desert while they were traveling with a caravan. The circumstances surrounding his disappearance suggest that he may have betrayed the caravan to the Kumaji.&#10;&#10;Firstly, it is mentioned that Tobias Whiting had profits tied up with a Kumaji moneylender, and thanks to an unspecified event, he will never see it again. This suggests that he had some sort of dealings with the Kumaji.&#10;&#10;Secondly, Steve and Mary spot the unicopter from a long way off, and Steve realizes that Tobias Whiting must have reached the Kumaji encampment by now if he escaped the crash-landing without injury. This further suggests that Tobias Whiting intentionally flew the unicopter to the Kumaji encampment.&#10;&#10;Lastly, Mary expresses her hatred for her father, saying that he is not asleep and is &quot;thinking&quot; about something. Steve then springs at Tobias Whiting, intending to kill him but ultimately deciding to hobble him instead. This suggests that Tobias Whiting's disappearance was a deliberate act of betrayal.&#10;&#10;Therefore, while the text does not explicitly state the reason for Tobias Whiting's disappearance, it strongly implies that he betrayed the caravan to the Kumaji." />
