termination to stay and warn the villagers. He may feel a sense of urgency to help his people and ensure their safety, as the old man has chosen to stay behind and face death.&#10;4. Additionally, Steve gives his canteen to the old man as a gesture of goodwill before he leaves, which may indicate that he feels pity for the old man and wants to help him in some way. This further highlights Steve's sense of responsibility and desire to help those in need, even if it means putting himself in danger.">
